    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Making Noise a Legal Issue Would Skirt Confrontations</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Susan Bruck Isaacson letter on August 6 responses to Peter Applebome's column on loud, obscene rap music being played by man at gas pump (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>After reading the responses regarding the man with the very loud radio in a gas station (Soapbox, Aug. 6), I thought of the effects on one's health, and specifically one's hearing. If citations were issued for noise pollution as they are for other infractions like littering or smoking in nonsmoking areas, then the need for debating confrontations of any kind and the possible ramifications would be avoided.</p>
        <p>SUSAN BRUCK ISAACSON  Warwick, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
